1 Initializing

#Installs libraries if not found already on computer
neededPackages <- c("tidyverse", "ggthemes", "readxl", "knitr", "tm", "lubridate")
                #add more packages if needed here
for (i in neededPackages){
  if (!is.element(i, .packages(all.available = TRUE)) ) {
    install.packages(i)
  }
  library(i,character.only = TRUE)
}

options(kableExtra_latex_packages = FALSE, knitr.table.format = "html", knitr.kable.NA = '')
#**Does not need to be changed if data files are in the same directory as this .Rmd**#
original_chart        <- read.csv("chart.csv", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
original_resources    <- read.csv("resources.csv")

original_students     <- read.csv("students.csv")
original_declarations <- readxl::read_excel("QTM_declarations_by_date.xlsx")

2 Cleaning Data

2.1 Fix Dates

#**Does not need to be changed unless format of chart.csv is changed**#
#Need to recreate graph of avg pageviews per week. Does not require time, so it will be removed
chart <- original_chart
stopwords = c(" PM",
              " AM",
              " EST",
              " EDT",
              ", 7:00",
              ", 8:00")

chart$Week.Start <- removeWords(chart$Week.Start, stopwords)

chart$Week.Start <- as.Date(chart$Week.Start, format = "%b %d, %Y")

2.2 Obtain Declaration Frequency

#***Does not need to be changed unless format of QTM_declarations_by_date.xlsx is changed***#

#Obtains declaration data and floors date to match chart data
declarations <- original_declarations

declarations$`Declaration date` <- 
  as.Date(declarations$`Declaration date`) %>% 
  floor_date(unit = "week")

#Obtains declaration frequency 
numDeclarations <- select(declarations,`Declaration date`) %>% 
  table() %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  setNames(c("Week.Start", "declarations"))

#Floors week start to match chart data
numDeclarations$Week.Start <- as.Date(numDeclarations$Week.Start)

#Adds frequency of declarations per week to the chart data. Merging is required to make a nice graph.
chart <- merge(chart, numDeclarations, by = "Week.Start", all.x = TRUE)
chart[is.na(chart)] <- 0

2.3 Obtain Significant Dates

#***Must be changed for each new school year***#

#Creates a data frame of the significant dates during the school year
## This tribble is for the 2019-2020 school year
significantDates <-
  tribble(~dateStart, ~`Significant Dates`,
          "2019-08-28", "Fall Classes Begin",
          "2019-11-01", "Capstone Application Deadline",
          "2019-12-10", "Fall Classes End",
          "2020-01-14", "Spring Classes Begin"
          )

#Floors dates to nearest week in order to match chart dates
significantDates$dateStart <- as.Date(significantDates$dateStart) %>% floor_date(unit = "week")

#Creates week interval by adding 7 days to floored date
significantDates$dateEnd <- significantDates$dateStart + 7

3 Graphs

3.1 Degree Declarations vs. Page Views

#**Some parts must be changed for each new school year**#

#Updated Graph (chart) including significant dates
ggplot(chart, aes(x = Week.Start, y = Avg.Page.Views)) +
    
    #Lines and Points
    geom_line(aes(y = declarations, col = "black")) +
    geom_line(aes(col = "#5daae9")) +
    geom_point(fill = "#2f8ee3", 
               stroke = 0.5, 
               color = "white", 
               shape = 21, 
               size = 3) +
    
    #Line Colors and Legend
    scale_color_identity(name = "Key", 
                         breaks = c("black", "#5daae9"),
                         labels = c("New Declarations", "Average Page Views per Student"),
                         guide = "legend") +
   
    #Highlights
     geom_rect(data = significantDates, 
               inherit.aes = FALSE, 
               aes(xmin = significantDates$dateStart, 
                   xmax = significantDates$dateEnd, 
                   ymin = -Inf, 
                   ymax = Inf,
                   fill = `Significant Dates`), 
               alpha = 0.2) +
  
    #Highlight Colors and Legend
    #**Change for each new school year**#
    scale_fill_manual(name = "Important Dates", guide = "legend",
                      
                      #Sets colors
                      values = c("Fall Classes Begin" = "orange", 
                                 "Capstone Application Deadline" = "yellow", 
                                 "Fall Classes End" = "red", 
                                 "Spring Classes Begin" =  "green"),
                      
                      #Sets the ordering of the legend
                      breaks = c("Fall Classes Begin", 
                                 "Capstone Application Deadline", 
                                 "Fall Classes End", 
                                 "Spring Classes Begin")) +
    
    #Scaling
    scale_x_date(date_breaks = "week", date_labels = "%m/%d") +
    scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, max(chart$Avg.Page.Views, chart$declarations)), 
                       breaks = seq(from = 0, 
                                    to = max(chart$Avg.Page.Views, chart$declarations), 
                                    by = 1)) + #Increase the 'by' parameter if the y-axis is too cluttered
    
    #Labels
    labs(title = "QTM Degree Declarations and QTMPrep Page Views Over Time",
       x = "Week (Month/Day starting Monday)", 
       y = "Frequency") +
    
    #Themes
    ggthemes::theme_tufte() +
#   theme_minimal(base_size = 12) + #Use this instead of ggthemes::theme_tufte() if you want gridlines
    theme(panel.grid.minor.y = element_blank(), 
          panel.grid.major.y = element_blank(), 
          axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90),
          text = element_text(family = "Times New Roman"))

3.2 QTMPrep Participation

#**Does not need to be changed unless:
##1. there are additional outliers (such as employees) that need to be removed
##2. there are more keywords to search for
##3. keywords need to be searched as lowercase**#

#Obtains essential information from data sets
students <- 
            original_students %>%
            filter(Full.Name != "Carolyne Armstrong") %>%   #Removes Carolyne because she is an employee (outlier)
            select(c("Page.Views", "Participations", "SIS.Id"))

#Uses regex to pull participations from student engagement, rather than .jpgs or .pngs
#Keywords: submit, submission, assignment, exercise, survey, upload, lab
#Note: Did not use to_lower() function because it was picking up syl`LAB`us (syllabus) when searching `lab`. This function relies on the first letter of the `resource` being capitalized.
resources <- 
  original_resources %>%
  filter(stringr::str_detect(Resource, "Submit|Submission|Assignment|Exercise|Survey|Upload|Lab"))
#**May need to change scaling with new data, particularly the y-axis because it is a density**#

ggplot(resources, aes(x = Participations)) +
  geom_density(aes(y = ..count../sum(..count..)), col = "green") +

  #Labels
  labs(title = "Density Distribution of QTMPrep Participation", 
       subtitle = "Based on Resources Used by Students",
       x = "Number of Participations", 
       y = "Density (% of Resources)") +
  
  #Scaling
  #coord_cartesian(xlim = c(i, j)) +          #If you want to zoom in to a particular spot
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0, 80),       #Use to set limits of x-axis
                     breaks = seq(from = 0,   #Use to set scaling of x-axis
                                  to = 80, 
                                  by = 5)) +  #Increase this if the x-axis is too cluttered
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format(accuracy = 0.1), 
                     limits = c(0, 0.035),        #Sets limits of y-axis as a percentage between [0, 1]
                     breaks = seq(from = 0,       #Use to set scaling between [0, 1]
                                  to = 0.035,     
                                  by = 0.005)) +
  
  #Themes
  ggthemes::theme_tufte()

3.3 Total Student Views

#**May need to change scaling with new data, particularly the y-axis because it is a density**#

#Density of Unique Student Views
#This graph uses "original_resources" because it measures everyone's views across everything, including pictures
ggplot(original_resources, aes(x = Students)) +
  geom_density(aes(y = ..count../sum(..count..)), col = "purple") +

  #Labels
  labs(title = "Density Distribution of QTMPrep Views", 
       subtitle = "Based on Resources Used by Students",
       x = "Number of Unique Student Views", 
       y = "Density (% of Resources)") +
  
  #Scaling
  #coord_cartesian(xlim = c(i, j)) + #If you want to zoom in to a particular spot
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0, floor((max(original_resources$Students)*1.1))), #Sets limit to 10% more than max
                     breaks = seq(from = 0, 
                                  to = floor((max(original_resources$Students)*1.1)), 
                                  by = 25)) +  #Increase this if the x-axis is too cluttered
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format(accuracy = 0.1), #Sets significant digits
                     limits = c(0, 0.03),      #Sets limits as a percentage between [0, 1] 
                     breaks = seq(from = 0,    #Sets breaks as a percentage between [0, 1]
                                  to = 0.03, 
                                  by = 0.005)) + 
  
  #Themes
  ggthemes::theme_tufte()

ggplot(students, aes(x = Page.Views)) +

  #Themes
